				<div id="post-183" class="hentry p3 post publish author-canuckaholic category-methodology category-web-design tag-agile tag-methodology-2 tag-process tag-ux is-full comments-open pings-open y2011 m03 d11 h05 slug-lean-ux-getting-out-of-the-deliverables-business"><h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://popdigital.ca/2011/03/11/lean-ux-getting-out-of-the-deliverables-business/" title="Permalink to Lean UX: Getting Out Of The Deliverables Business" rel="bookmark">Lean UX: Getting Out Of The Deliverables Business</a></h2>
<div class="entry-meta"><span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">By </span><span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://popdigital.ca/author/admin/" title="View all posts by Adrian">Adrian</a></span><span class="meta-sep meta-sep-entry-date"> | </span><span class="meta-prep meta-prep-entry-date">Published: </span><span class="entry-date"><abbr class="published" title="2011-03-11T12:02:52-0700">March 11, 2011</abbr></span></div><!-- .entry-meta -->
					<div class="entry-content">
<p>Check out <a title="Lean UX" href="http://www.smashingmagazine.com/2011/03/07/lean-ux-getting-out-of-the-deliverables-business/" target="_blank">this great article</a> on Smashing Magazine on Lean UX, a methodology rooted in Agile.</p>
<p>Excerpt:</p>
<blockquote><p>&#8220;Inspired by Lean and Agile development theories, Lean UX is the practice of bringing the true nature of our work to light faster, with less emphasis on deliverables and greater focus on the actual experience being designed.&#8221;</p></blockquote>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-184" title="lean_ux_process" src="http://popdigital.ca/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/lean_ux_process.jpg" alt="Lean UX process" width="500" height="134" /></p>
