				<div id="post-126" class="hentry p5 post publish author-canuckaholic category-business-tips category-words-of-wisdom tag-agile tag-business-tip-2 tag-sitepoint is-full comments-open pings-open y2011 m03 d09 h04 slug-business-tip-of-the-day-march-9-2011"><h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://popdigital.ca/2011/03/09/business-tip-of-the-day-march-9-2011/" title="Permalink to Business Tip of the Day for March 9th, 2011" rel="bookmark">Business Tip of the Day for March 9th, 2011</a></h2>
<div class="entry-meta"><span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">By </span><span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://popdigital.ca/author/admin/" title="View all posts by Adrian">Adrian</a></span><span class="meta-sep meta-sep-entry-date"> | </span><span class="meta-prep meta-prep-entry-date">Published: </span><span class="entry-date"><abbr class="published" title="2011-03-09T11:15:47-0700">March 9, 2011</abbr></span></div><!-- .entry-meta -->
					<div class="entry-content">
<p><em>Be Agile </em></p>
<p>The more agile and flexible your business is, the better your chances for success in an ever-changing industry environment.</p>
<p><em>Keep an Eye on the Competition</em></p>
<p>The market for low-cost web design is becoming saturated with competing services and service providers. If you are consistently seeing competitors enter your sphere, it could be time to narrow your company&#8217;s focus or change direction altogether.</p>
<p>- Paraphrased from SitePoint&#8217;s Tribune #536 &#8211; The Business of Change</p>
<div class="tweetthis" style="text-align:right;"><p> <a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" class="tt" href="http://twitter.com/share?url=http://popdigital.ca/2011/03/09/business-tip-of-the-day-march-9-2011/&text=Business+Tip+of+the+Day+for+March+9th%2C+2011&via=tweetthisplugin&related=richardxthripp%2Ctweetthisplugin" title="Post to Twitter"><img class="nothumb" src="http://popdigital.ca/wp-content/plugins/tweet-this/icons/en/twitter/tt-twitter6.png" alt="Post to Twitter" /></a></p></div>
										</div><!-- .entry-content -->
					<div class="entry-utility"><span class="cat-links">Posted in <a href="http://popdigital.ca/category/business-tips/" title="View all posts in Business Tips" rel="category tag">Business Tips</a>, <a href="http://popdigital.ca/category/words-of-wisdom/" title="View all posts in Words of Wisdom" rel="category tag">Words of Wisdom</a></span> <span class="meta-sep meta-sep-tag-links">|</span><span class="tag-links"> Tagged <a href="http://popdigital.ca/tag/agile/" rel="tag">Agile</a>, <a href="http://popdigital.ca/tag/business-tip-2/" rel="tag">business tip</a>, <a href="http://popdigital.ca/tag/sitepoint/" rel="tag">SitePoint</a></span> <span class="meta-sep meta-sep-comments-link">|</span> <span class="comments-link"><a href="http://popdigital.ca/2011/03/09/business-tip-of-the-day-march-9-2011/#comments" title="Comment on Business Tip of the Day for March 9th, 2011">Leave a comment</a></span></div><!-- .entry-utility -->
				</div><!-- #post -->

			
				<div id="post-52" class="hentry p6 post publish author-canuckaholic category-web-design category-wordpress untagged is-full comments-open pings-open y2011 m03 d07 h02 alt slug-adding-post-excerpts-to-your-wordpress-static-front-page"><h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://popdigital.ca/2011/03/07/adding-post-excerpts-to-your-wordpress-static-front-page/" title="Permalink to Adding Post Excerpts to your WordPress Static Front Page" rel="bookmark">Adding Post Excerpts to your WordPress Static Front Page</a></h2>
<div class="entry-meta"><span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">By </span><span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://popdigital.ca/author/admin/" title="View all posts by Adrian">Adrian</a></span><span class="meta-sep meta-sep-entry-date"> | </span><span class="meta-prep meta-prep-entry-date">Published: </span><span class="entry-date"><abbr class="published" title="2011-03-07T09:24:26-0700">March 7, 2011</abbr></span></div><!-- .entry-meta -->
					<div class="entry-content">
<p>I would have thought that solutions to this scenario would have been all over Google, but alas I had to dig to find snippets of information that eventually allowed me to write the code that I wanted.</p>
<p><strong>What I wanted:</strong> A list of my top 5 blog posts to appear on my WordPress site&#8217;s static homepage, with the blog&#8217;s title and a small amount of the blog&#8217;s text. I also wanted the &#8220;more&#8221; text to be a link to the actual blog post.</p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p>1. Add the following to your theme&#8217;s functions.php file (inside the &lt;?php &#8230; ?&gt; tags):</p>
<pre>function home_excerpt_length($length) {
return 10; // The length of the excerpt text in characters
}

function home_excerpt_more($more) {
global $post;
return ' &lt;a href="'. get_permalink($post-&gt;ID) . '"&gt;[more...]&lt;/a&gt;';
}</pre>
<p>2. Add the following to your front-page.php file (or whatever template file you are using) at the spot on the page where you want the blog excerpts to appear:</p>
<pre>&lt;?php
query_posts('posts_per_page=5');
add_filter('excerpt_length', 'home_excerpt_length');
add_filter('excerpt_more', 'home_excerpt_more');
if (have_posts()) :
while (have_posts()) :
the_post();
echo "&lt;h3&gt;";
the_title();
echo "&lt;/h3&gt;";
the_excerpt();
endwhile;
endif;
?&gt;</pre>
<div class="tweetthis" style="text-align:right;"><p> <a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" class="tt" href="http://twitter.com/share?url=http://popdigital.ca/2011/03/07/adding-post-excerpts-to-your-wordpress-static-front-page/&text=Adding+Post+Excerpts+to+your+WordPress+Static+Front+Page&via=tweetthisplugin&related=richardxthripp%2Ctweetthisplugin" title="Post to Twitter"><img class="nothumb" src="http://popdigital.ca/wp-content/plugins/tweet-this/icons/en/twitter/tt-twitter6.png" alt="Post to Twitter" /></a></p></div>
										</div><!-- .entry-content -->
					<div class="entry-utility"><span class="cat-links">Posted in <a href="http://popdigital.ca/category/web-design/" title="View all posts in Web Design" rel="category tag">Web Design</a>, <a href="http://popdigital.ca/category/web-design/wordpress/" title="View all posts in WordPress" rel="category tag">WordPress</a></span> <span class="meta-sep meta-sep-tag-links">|</span> <span class="comments-link"><a href="http://popdigital.ca/2011/03/07/adding-post-excerpts-to-your-wordpress-static-front-page/#comments" title="Comment on Adding Post Excerpts to your WordPress Static Front Page">Leave a comment</a></span></div><!-- .entry-utility -->
				</div><!-- #post -->

			
				<div id="post-378" class="hentry p7 post publish author-canuckaholic category-work-examples tag-allison-wonderland tag-fashion tag-web-design-2 is-full comments-closed pings-closed y2011 m02 d25 h05 slug-allison-wondeland-website"><h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://popdigital.ca/2011/02/25/allison-wondeland-website/" title="Permalink to Website: Allison Wondeland" rel="bookmark">Website: Allison Wondeland</a></h2>
<div class="entry-meta"><span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">By </span><span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://popdigital.ca/author/admin/" title="View all posts by Adrian">Adrian</a></span><span class="meta-sep meta-sep-entry-date"> | </span><span class="meta-prep meta-prep-entry-date">Published: </span><span class="entry-date"><abbr class="published" title="2011-02-25T12:51:08-0700">February 25, 2011</abbr></span></div><!-- .entry-meta -->
					<div class="entry-content">
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-381" title="allison_wonderland_558x300" src="http://popdigital.ca/wp-content/uploads/2009/02/allison_wonderland_558x300.jpg" alt="Allison Wonderland" width="558" height="300" /></p>
<h2>About:</h2>
<p>Allison Wonderland is the website of one of Vancouver&#8217;s premiere fashion designers, Allison Smith. Allison started her own unique line in 1998, following her graduation from Kwantlen College&#8217;s acclaimed Fashion Design &amp; Technology program and several years spent in Montreal&#8217;s rag trade. Since then, Allison Wonderland Clothing has continued to provide satisfaction to the style-savvy of North America and Japan.</p>
<h2>Type of Project:</h2>
<p>Website. Underlying server architecture is LAMP.</p>
<h2>URL:</h2>
<p><a title="Allison Wonderland" href="http://allisonwonderland.ca" target="_blank">allisonwonderland.ca</a></p>
<h2>What We Did:</h2>
<div class="column">
<ul>
<li>HTML/XHTML</li>
<li>CSS</li>
<li>PHP</li>
<li>Javascript</li>
<li>jQuery</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="clearFloats"></div>
